We want to saturate our multiplier result and adder result.
We work with notation Q0.7 We consider the case of:

a)0.1111111 x 0.1111111 = 0.9922 * 0.9922
b)0.1111111 x 1.0000000 = 0.9922 * -1
c)1.0000000 x 0.1111111 = -1 * 0.9922
d)1.0000000 x 1.0000000 = -1 * -1

a)127*127 = 16129 = 00.1111110 0000001 ->  0.1111010 0.9531 correct 
b)127*128 = 16256 = 11.0000001 0000000 ->  1.0000001 -0.9922 correct
c)128*127 = 16256 = 11.0000001 0000000 ->  1.0000001 -0.9922 correct

d)128*128 = 16384 = 01.0000000 0000000 ->  1.0000000 -1     wrong, should be -1*-1 = 1

Sum issues:

a)0.1111111 + 0.1111111 = 0.9922 + 0.9922 
b)0.1111111 + 1.0000000 = 0.9922 + -1
c)1.0000000 + 0.1111111 = -1 + 0.9922
d)1.0000000 + 1.0000000 = -1 + -1

a)127+127 = 254 = 01.1111110 -> 1.1111110 wrong, should be positive
b)127+128 = 255 = 01.1111111 -> 1.1111111 -0.0078 correct
c)128+127 = 255 = 01.1111111 -> 1.1111111 -0.0078 correct
d)128+128 = 256 = 10.0000000 -> 0.0000000 wrong, should be -2


